<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/59025733-jens-raab"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1532354950i/59025733._UX100_CR0,26,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/59025733-jens-raab">Jens Raab</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s been a while that I read the book and watched the movie (the longer TV version) but from what I remember the movie was quite OK. Very entertainin<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's been a while that I read the book and watched the movie (the longer TV version) but from what I remember the movie was quite OK. Very entertaining but there are some differences to the novel.<br />So I would say that the adaption could be a bit more faithful and compressed the plot (which was to be expected given the length of the novel) and therefore isn't perfect but half as good? Yes! ;-)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
