<span id="freeTextContainer2679238841525856625">I actually really liked this for what it was. It felt a little bit like going home. This genre and style of book is what I used to read and got me to love to read decades ago and so it felt very familiar and comfortable to me. It is a fairly long, but who doesn’t have a few extra 20 hours on their hands right now? #coronaquarantine There was no lag, it kept the same pace throughout the book and if nothing else actually picked up towards the end. I didn’t know how it was going to be resolved but </span>
  <span id="freeText2679238841525856625" style="display:none">I actually really liked this for what it was. It felt a little bit like going home. This genre and style of book is what I used to read and got me to love to read decades ago and so it felt very familiar and comfortable to me. It is a fairly long, but who doesn’t have a few extra 20 hours on their hands right now? #coronaquarantine There was no lag, it kept the same pace throughout the book and if nothing else actually picked up towards the end. I didn’t know how it was going to be resolved but I was very happy with how it ended. I was very happy to hear the authors historical notes to know exactly how much was true and wasn’t. But do not read or listen to those in the beginning...they would be a major spoiler. </span>
